                      <td>&nbsp;</td>
                      <td width="100%" valign="top"> 
                        <p>The Resume Center is the most important 
                          tool available to you on personnel.com. Using the Resume Center you can 
                          create your online profile, build and edit 
                          multiple online resumes and apply for listed jobs. You can even elect to make your resume(s) searchable by employers.</p>
                        <p><STRONG>Build a Resume</STRONG><br>
                          To build a resume, go to your Resume 
                          Center and click on <a href="/registered/logged/resume/newResume/index.asp">Add a New Resume</a>. You 
                          will be guided step-by-step until you have a complete online 
                          resume. Be sure to provide all of the <a href="/registered/logged/resume/resumeHelp/help.asp">required information</a>.<br> if you already have a resume that is available for upload the process will be much quicker.<br>
                          </p>
                        <p><STRONG>Activating and Deactivating a Resume</STRONG><br>
Activating a resume active allows potential employers to freely browse your resume and increases your online exposure.						
                          To make a resume searchable by potential employers you 
                          will have to mark it as active. To do this go to the Resume 
                          Center, select the resume you wish to change, and click either <strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>Deactivate</strong> depending 
                          on it's current status.</p>
                        <p><STRONG>Edit a Resume</STRONG><br>
                          From the Resume 
                          Center scroll down to the resume you would like 
                          to edit and click on the <strong>Edit</strong> option. This will take you through a step by step editing process that will allow you to change any aspects 
                          of your online resume.</p>
                        <p><STRONG>Delete a Resume</STRONG><br>
                          From the Resume 
                          Center choose the resume you want to delete 
                          and click the <strong>Delete</strong> option. 
                          Your resume will be displayed and you will have to option to permanently delete it or to cancel.</p>
                        <p><STRONG>View a Resume</STRONG><br>
                          From your Resume 
                          Center choose the resume you want to view 
                          and click on the <strong>View</strong> option. 
                          You will taken to a full view of your resume and have access to all your available resume options.</p>
                        <p><STRONG>Submitting a Resume</STRONG><br>
                          To submit a resume to an employer, click on <a href="/registered/logged/search/index.asp">Search Jobs</a> from the main menu. Utilize the optional search criteria to find a job position you wish to apply for, and then click on the job title to view more details. Click on the <strong>Apply</strong> button at the bottom of the page and continue through the prompts.</p>
                        <p><STRONG>Resume Advice/Info</STRONG><br>
